==Description==
Level 646 is a large, enclosed shopping mall that closely resembles Romanian malls built in the late 1990s. The interior is completely sealed off from the outside. No windows, skylights, or exterior exits have been observed. The lights throughout the level remain on, but there are no signs that the mall is still in use.

The layout includes long hallways, open atriums, closed stores, and several sets of escalators. As a person moves deeper into the mall, the layout becomes harder to understand. Hallways begin to repeat with small changes. Atriums reconnect at odd angles. Areas that should be separate slowly start to feel the same. Even when landmarks are tracked on purpose, navigation often fails. This matches patterns seen in [[Phenomenon 14]], though the effect usually appears slowly rather than all at once.

The lighting gives off a dim, yellow glow and produces a steady electrical hum. Flickering is rare, but the lights often feel weak or strained. Long exposure can cause headaches, dizziness, or general exhaustion. The air is stale, with no noticeable airflow. Footsteps are often quiet or fully absorbed by the floor, while soft voices can travel far across open spaces. At times, sounds seem to come from directions that do not match the visible layout.

Most stores are sealed behind metal shutters. Many of these shutters feel warm to the touch, even though no light is visible inside. Behind them, shops are still stocked with clothing, electronics, and packaged items. The products appear unused, but they do not clearly belong to any specific place or time period. Mannequins are common, especially in groups of nearby stores. Many are damaged or missing parts. Some reports suggest their positions change between visits, though no one has seen them move directly.

Floor conditions change from area to area. Some floors are smooth and shiny. Others are worn down or uneven. Elevation changes happen often without warning. Floors may slope or rise over short distances with no visual signs. Atrium railings usually look intact, but they are not reliable. Their placement does not always line up with the surrounding structure, and leaning on them is unsafe.
Mall directories are scattered throughout the level, but they cannot be trusted. Maps often leave out large sections, label areas incorrectly, or show layouts that do not match reality. “YOU ARE HERE” markers almost never show the correct location. Following directory paths often leads in circles or back into areas already explored.

Time behaves strangely in Level 646. People frequently lose track of how long they have been inside. Travel times between familiar locations can change from one trip to the next. Electronic devices may show incorrect times or fail to track time passing. These effects are consistent with [[Phenomenon 57]] and tend to worsen the longer someone stays in the level.

Escalators and elevators work only some of the time. Escalators may stop suddenly or restart after long periods. Elevators sometimes open onto dark, unfinished, or blocked spaces that do not match any known layout. Using elevators for extended travel is strongly discouraged.

Food courts and cafes appear in random locations. Eating food found in the level has been linked to mental fog, emotional heaviness, and trouble focusing. For this reason, consumption is not recommended. Any food brought into this level has been affected as the food is to quickly lose appetite and rot; no matter the conditions.

==Entities==
[[Entity 29]] has been observed in Level 646, most often inside abandoned stores, anchor shops, and dressing rooms. Because the level already contains many regular mannequins, it is difficult to tell active instances of [[Entity 29]] apart from the environment. Most sightings happen in low light areas or places with little foot traffic. When inactive, the entity remains perfectly still, posed like a store display and often dressed in outdated clothing found within the mall.

[[Entity 29]] follows the same basic behavior seen in other levels. It does not move while being watched and only relocates when unobserved. In Level 646, mirrors, glass storefronts, and security cameras can interfere with detection. This may delay awareness of movement. Reports suggest the entity slowly repositions itself along looping hallways or near escalators, using the distorted layout to close distance without being noticed. No sounds or speech have been confirmed.

Hostile behavior has been recorded when wanderers lose sight of the entity or attempt to escape without maintaining visual contact. Attacks are sudden and usually occur in narrow hallways, dressing rooms, or service corridors. Because the mall layout is confusing and full of distractions, encounters with [[Entity 29]] are considered especially dangerous, even though its behavior rules are known. Avoidance is recommended. Limit time spent near mannequin heavy areas and always stay visually aware when passing through inactive stores.

